1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. c4 d5 4. Nc3 { D37 Queen's Gambit Declined: Three Knights Variation } 4... Bd7?! { (-0.08 → 0.78) Inaccuracy. dxc4 was best. } { A key to beating higher-rated players is to move them out off theory quickly. } (4... dxc4 5. e4 Bb4 6. Bg5 c5 7. Bxc4 h6 8. Bxf6 Qxf6 9. O-O) 5. cxd5 exd5 6. Bg5?! { (0.95 → 0.40) Inaccuracy. Qb3 was best. } (6. Qb3 { Dyshkant, Fedor Nikolaevich - Baroin, Bernard, 1/2-1/2, WS/CCM/B/1, 2019, https://lichess.org/GoBdLkfa } 6... c5 7. Bg5 Nc6 8. Bxf6 gxf6 9. e3 c4 10. Qc2 Bg4) 6... Be7? { (0.40 → 1.80) Mistake. c6 was best. } { Bxf6 just wins the d5 pawn. } { [%csl Bf6,Rd5][%cal Bg5f6,Ye7f6] } (6... c6 { Moving into a Semi-Slav like position } 7. e3 Bf5 8. Bd3 Bxd3 9. Qxd3 Be7 10. Bxf6 Bxf6 11. e4) 7. Qb3?! { (1.80 → 0.92) Inaccuracy. Bxf6 was best. } { Missing it. } (7. Bxf6 Bxf6 8. Nxd5 Bg4 9. Nxf6+ Qxf6 10. e3 Nd7 11. Rc1 Bxf3 12. Qxf3 Qxf3 13. gxf3 c6) 7... Bc6 { I'm safe for now, but my opponent has the initiative. } 8. Ne5 h6 { Trying to dislodge the bishop. } 9. Bh4?! { (1.01 → 0.35) Inaccuracy. Nxc6 was best. } (9. Nxc6 Nxc6 10. Bxf6 Bxf6 11. Qxb7) 9... Nfd7? { (0.35 → 1.56) Mistake. Nbd7 was best. } { Trying to free up my position by trading. } { [%csl Bd7][%cal Bf6d7] } (9... Nbd7 10. Bxf6 Bxf6 11. Nf3 O-O 12. e3 Nb6 13. Bd3 a5 14. a4 Be8 15. O-O c6 16. Ne5) 10. Nxd5?? { (1.56 → -2.03) Blunder. Nxc6 was best. } { A game losing blunder. My opponent is trying to end the game with sacrifices, though there are none. } (10. Nxc6 bxc6 11. Bxe7 Qxe7 12. e3 O-O 13. Rc1 Qd6 14. Bd3 Nf6 15. Qc2 Nbd7 16. O-O Rab8) 10... Bxh4 { [%csl Bf7,Yc7,Yc6][%cal Bb3f7,Be5f7,Yd5c7,Ye5c6] } 11. Nxc7+?? { (-2.15 → -7.61) Blunder. Nxc6 was best. } { After Qxc7 I get the d8 square, saving my king. } (11. Nxc6 bxc6 12. Nc3 c5 13. Qb7 cxd4 14. Qxa8 dxc3 15. Qe4+ Be7 16. bxc3 Nc5 17. Qe3 O-O) 11... Qxc7 12. Qxf7+ Kd8 13. Ng6 { Trying to win some material and continue the attack } 13... Qa5+! { Here I found a combination to trade queen's leaving me 3 pieces up. } 14. Kd1 Qa4+! 15. Kc1 Be4! { My favorite move, threating to checkmate or take the knight on g6. } 16. b3 Qc6+ { White resigns. } { And now I will be three pieces up. } 17. Qc4 Qxc4+ 18. bxc4 Bxg6 19. g3 Bf6 20. e3 Be4 21. Rg1 Nc5 22. Be2 Nd3+ 23. Bxd3 Bxd3 24. c5 b6 25. Kd2 Bg6 26. Rac1 bxc5 27. Rxc5 Nd7 28. Rd5 Ke7 29. Rc1 Rac8 30. Rxc8 Rxc8 31. f4 Rc2+ 32. Kd1 Rxh2 33. f5 Bh5+ 34. Kc1 Bg5 35. Kb1 Bxe3 36. f6+ gxf6 37. Rb5 Bg6+ 38. Ka1 Bxd4+ 39. Rb2 Bxb2# 0-1


